replies.body:
My preferred build...

Off the fountain: {{item:3302}} {{item:2003}} {{item:3340}} 

Base Items: {{item:3097}} {{item:3044}} {{item:3047}} {{item:3116}} 

Typical 6 item build: {{item:3116}} {{item:3047}} {{item:3078}} {{item:3143}} {{item:3065}} {{item:3135}} 

I've tried the AD build with Tri Force rush and hated it every time. It makes me cringe when I see a second AD item before Rylai's. Conversely, I've also tried the flat AP build with Gunblade and Deathcap ala pre-rework, and never even gotten it off the ground.

I play tanks so much I tend to build all champs with more durability then recommended, which to an extent made me happy to see that {{champion:82}}  was being reworked to be more like a tank. As much as I wish his identity was better executed in the rework (master of pain and suffering? Better give him an ally heal!), latching onto the tanky hybrid bruiser build has at least given me a decent amount of satisfaction.

Stay strong brethren! You can't kill the METAL.

I'm tempted to say {{item:3116}} isn't a preferable item on Morde.  Dont get me wrong, it is nice but the slow just never feels good enough for my taste.

Haven't had time to try this build yet but im going to try {{item:3053}} {{item:3151}} {{item:3078}} {{item:3083}} {{item:3026}} with maybe {{item:1330}} 

Good luck finding the right build!  Kinda feels like a gold rush for playing Morde XP
